.PARA
^MOST OF THE READ AND WRITE LICENSES ARE ARRANGED IN A HIERARCHY SO THAT
A READ OR WRITE LICENSE THAT IS MORE POWERFUL THAN OTHERS IMPLIES
POSSESSION OF THE LESS POWERFUL LICENSES AS WELL.  ^THESE READ AND WRITE
LICENSES ARE LISTED BELOW IN ORDER OF MOST POWERFUL TO LEAST POWERFUL.
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.INDENT 15
^READ ^ABSOLUTE          ^WRITE ^ABSOLUTE
.INDENT 15
^READ ^FILES             ^WRITE ^FILES
.INDENT 15
^READ ^PROJECT           ^WRITE ^PROJECT
.FILL.JUST
.PARA
^THUS, A ^READ ^ABSOLUTE LICENSE IMPLIES THE ^READ ^FILES AND ^READ IN 
^PROJECT LICENSES.
.PARA
^EACH WRITE LICENSE LISTED ABOVE ALSO IMPLIES THE CORRESPONDING READ LICENSE
AS WELL AS THE LESS POWERFUL READ AND WRITE LICENSES.  ^FOR EXAMPLE, AN
OPERATOR HOLDING THE ^WRITE ^FILES LICENSE ALSO HOLDS THE ^WRITE IN
^PROJECT, ^READ ^FILES, AND ^READ ^PROJECT LICENSES.
.SKIP 1
