.INDENT 5
^THE <PPN COMMAND IS SELF EXPLANITORY. (SEE COMMAND SUMMARY AND SAMPLE)
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 5
^IN GENERAL, ^ACCOUNT ^SUPERVISOR (WHICH IS OBTAINED WHEN YOU LOG INTO
<OPER) AND ^READ ^FILE LICENSE ARE NECESSARY TO OUTPUT INFORMATION IN
THE <NONAME PROGRAM.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 5
^THE <NONAME USER MAY EITHER TYPE IN AN ENTIRE COMMAND STRING OR
INPUT PARTS OF THE COMMAND STRING TO <NONAME PROMPTS.
^FOR EXAMPLE, THE USER MAY TYPE:
.SKIP 1
.CENTER
<LIST <USER <ABCD
.SKIP 1
OR HE MAY TYPE ONE WORD AT A TIME AND THE PROGRAM WILL ASK FOR THE
NEXT PART OF THE COMMAND STRING.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 5
^NORMALLY THE PROGRAM WILL REPEAT A QUESTION IF AN INVALID REPLY IS GIVEN.
^IF THE USER GETS A QUESTION HE/SHE DOES NOT KNOW THE ANSWER TO, HE/SHE CAN FORCE THE
PROGRAM BACK TO THE COMMAND DISPATCHER BY ENTERING A QUESTION
MARK AS A REPLY TO ANY YES OR NO QUESTION OR WHENEVER THE
PROGRAM IS REQUESTING A USER NAME.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 5
^WITHIN THE ^SAMPLE ^RUN BELOW, SEVERAL OF THE PARAMETERS REFERENCED
ARE ABBREVIATED IN THE OUTPUT FROM <NONAME.
^A BREAKDOWN AND EXPLANATION OF THESE PARAMETERS IS AS FOLLOWS:
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
^^
.NO FLAG CAPIT
LICENSE - ACT.SUP. = ACCOUNT SUPERVISOR
        TYM. = TYMSHARE
.SKIP 1
MSG - WHAT IS DONE WITH TYMSHARE MESSAGE AT LOGIN.
	SUP=SUPRESS MESSAGE
	TYP=TYPE MESSAGE
.SKIP 1
ZONE - TIME ZONE
	D=DAYLIGHT SAVINGS
	S=STANDARD
.SKIP 1
DISC - WHAT IS DONE IF THE TELEPHONE LINE DISCONNECTS.
	LOG=LOGOUT JOB
	DET=DETACH JOB
.SKIP 1
DET-T=DETACH, 15 MIN. TIME OUT SET
.SKIP 1
CORE - MAXIMUM AMOUNT OF USER CORE
	DEF = SYSTEM DEFAULT
.SKIP 1
GFD - ACCESS TO GFD
     ACC = ACCESS TO GFD
     NO = NO ACCESS TO GFD
.SKIP 3
BTNA ACCOUNTING AND USERS
^REVISION 2; 10/26/93
.PAGE
MODE - THE MODE THE USER RUNS UNDER
     TYM - XEXEC OR TYMEX MODE
     PDP10 - MONITOR OR PDP MODE
     GE - GENERAL ELECTRIC SUDS MODE
